FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - MALAYSIA (PENINSULAR)
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html
Date: 13 Feb, 1999
Source: OIE Reports

See also: 12 February 1999
Follow-up report No. 1
Text of a fax received on 13 February 1999 from Dr Mohd Nordin Mohd Nor,
Director General of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Kuala
Lumpur:
End of previous report period: 8 February 1999 (see Disease Information, 12
[5], 16, dated 12 February 1999).
End of this report period: 13 February 1999.
New outbreak:
Location: Jelebu district, State of Negeri Sembilan (2o 58' N - 102o 04' E)
No. of outbreaks: 1
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1999: two (2).
Description of affected population in the new outbreak: the affected
livestock are owned by smallholders and are under an extensive management
system.
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:
species bov
susceptible 390
cases 1
deaths 0
destroyed 0
slaughtered 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Kota Bahru Regional Veterinary
Laboratory, Kelantan.
B. Diagnostic tests used: ELISA (viral antigen detection).
C. Causal agent: FMD virus type O.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: further investigations into the
epidemiology of the disease are being undertaken.
B. Mode of spread: contact with livestock.
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine and movement control
inside the country; vaccination.
--
